cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational geometry, specifically the computation of diameter and radius within a polygonal domain. This falls under the category of cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also introduces a graph of oriented distances, which suggests a connection to graph theory and algorithms, falling under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of efficient algorithms and complexity analysis suggests a connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
